Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2 — Intercept back navigation and conditionally cancel it:**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` (hardware/gesture back) and handle the Shell back button via `BackButtonBehavior`:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            ShowExitConfirmation();
            return true; // cancel navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async void ShowExitConfirmation()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
        {
            _hasUnsavedChanges = false;
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
        }
    }
}
```

**3 — Custom "Cancel" back button in Shell:**

In your XAML, replace the default back arrow with a text-based button that calls the same confirmation logic:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Title="Edit Product">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior Command="{Binding BackCommand}"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            IconOverride="" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

public EditProductPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BackCommand = new Command(OnBackRequested);
    BindingContext = this;
}

private void OnBackRequested()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        ShowExitConfirmation();
    else
        Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` returning `true` cancels Android/device back.
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the Shell toolbar back button — it won't navigate automatically, so you control it entirely.
- `TextOverride="Cancel"` with an empty `IconOverride` swaps the arrow for text.
